WEBVTT

00:17.684 --> 00:20.937
Sensei, please keep teaching me how...

00:21.438 --> 00:22.647
Ah, no.

00:22.731 --> 00:27.318
Sensei, please continue to honor me
with your teachings of the sword!

00:28.361 --> 00:29.904
Of course.

00:30.989 --> 00:33.825
With him here, we’ve got
nothing to worry about anymore.

00:33.908 --> 00:35.535
I owe him everything!

00:35.618 --> 00:37.787
And he's my sword master! Ow!

00:37.871 --> 00:40.915
Even at a time like this,
you’re still the same, Sensei.

00:40.999 --> 00:43.042
It actually kind of makes me
feel relieved.

00:44.753 --> 00:46.546
You're totally underestimating me.

00:55.513 --> 00:57.015
I’m used to it.

01:01.519 --> 01:03.146
Tenza!

01:13.281 --> 01:15.658
Hurry... Run...

01:30.048 --> 01:32.175
Those who take from others
cannot understand.

01:33.927 --> 01:37.305
Those who are taken from
cannot ever forget!

03:18.197 --> 03:20.867
I kept cutting him down
over and over as he regenerated,

03:20.950 --> 03:22.493
forcing him to burn through his Tao.

03:23.077 --> 03:26.623
It’s not a fatal wound, but his
regeneration has slowed considerably,

03:26.706 --> 03:29.125
and he looks like he’s aged too.

03:29.208 --> 03:31.628
He shouldn’t be able to do much more.

03:41.095 --> 03:45.516
Anything without life can be controlled
with just a small amount of Tao.

03:46.184 --> 03:47.769
Die, humans!

04:01.783 --> 04:04.160
I’ll recover while I have the chance.

04:04.744 --> 04:07.121
He’s just as worn down.

04:07.956 --> 04:12.543
He’s shortening his own life
by repeatedly attacking with Tao.

04:16.506 --> 04:17.423
Sensei!

04:20.510 --> 04:22.929
Child’s play... Useless!

04:24.430 --> 04:27.016
Tameshi Ittoryu: Murashigure!

04:38.194 --> 04:40.071
He didn’t get my Tanden.

04:41.155 --> 04:42.323
"Clink"?

04:56.587 --> 04:59.590
You’re on the verge of death too!

05:00.550 --> 05:02.468
What the hell is wrong with you?!

05:04.846 --> 05:06.097
Stay back!

05:11.811 --> 05:12.895
Sen--

05:20.820 --> 05:22.155
Huh, huh?!

05:30.204 --> 05:32.373
What are you?

05:32.457 --> 05:35.501
You’d shorten your own life

05:35.585 --> 05:37.378
for someone who’s already dead.

05:38.129 --> 05:39.964
Why go this far?

05:44.010 --> 05:45.887
I haven’t done anything yet.

05:45.970 --> 05:48.723
I can’t feel pain. I can't feel sorrow.

05:49.432 --> 05:51.184
Not yet.

05:51.893 --> 05:53.644
Even anger is a nuisance.

05:54.645 --> 05:56.189
As long as you’re still alive.

05:57.607 --> 05:59.650
Everything comes after I kill you.

06:00.485 --> 06:02.904
Despair and grief come after that too!

06:03.696 --> 06:06.157
Now then, how many hundreds
more times do I have to cut you

06:06.949 --> 06:08.034
before you die?

06:08.743 --> 06:12.080
This is bad. Bad, bad, bad...

06:12.163 --> 06:13.414
I’ve got to do something.

06:14.040 --> 06:15.249
Something...

06:29.097 --> 06:30.181
Don’t panic.

06:30.890 --> 06:34.060
Tao shouldn’t recover that quickly.

06:43.528 --> 06:46.322
Did you think you were just one step away?

06:46.405 --> 06:48.449
Don’t underestimate me, human.

06:49.325 --> 06:50.701
One of my comrades

06:50.785 --> 06:54.497
is always both male and female,
circulating yin and yang alone

06:54.580 --> 06:55.957
to refine Tao.

06:56.582 --> 06:58.000
I imitated that.

06:59.252 --> 07:02.046
Maintaining both sexes
is pretty difficult,

07:02.130 --> 07:03.840
but I don’t have a choice right now.

07:03.923 --> 07:05.216
And besides...

07:07.301 --> 07:08.511
So, it's true.

07:08.594 --> 07:10.096
I always thought

07:10.888 --> 07:14.475
that if I can partially transform,
then Kishikai should be the same.

07:17.478 --> 07:20.731
So, how many hundreds more times...

07:21.357 --> 07:22.817
shall we continue?

07:29.073 --> 07:32.493
I will... settle this!

07:32.577 --> 07:36.247
I’m used to your tricks.

07:53.347 --> 07:54.557
"Tricks".

07:56.267 --> 07:59.020
I don’t care. That’s who I am.

08:06.819 --> 08:10.740
The one who gave me these scars
was my mother, a traveling performer.

08:13.326 --> 08:16.996
A blind child dodging customers’
wooden swords, that was our act.

08:17.079 --> 08:20.124
"The child of a sword god
who can read the blade without seeing."

08:20.208 --> 08:21.042
CHILD OF A SWORD GOD

08:21.125 --> 08:24.003
My mother and I
were just desperate to survive.

08:26.088 --> 08:30.134
The scars were part of the performance,
but I was born blind.

08:30.218 --> 08:34.764
Ever since I was little, I could feel
the waves. I sensed the world through Tao.

08:34.847 --> 08:36.224
So for me, it was an easy act.

08:39.393 --> 08:43.397
Hearing of our reputation,
Soroku Kengyo took me into the Todoza.

08:43.481 --> 08:46.359
Through his connections,
I was allowed to enter the Yamada school.

08:47.151 --> 08:51.155
For a poor performer and her child,
it was a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

08:55.743 --> 09:00.873
A child, and a blind one at that,
is so skilled with the sword.

09:00.957 --> 09:02.542
Where did those scars come from?

09:03.125 --> 09:06.254
This child has a famed
swordsman for a father.

09:06.337 --> 09:10.216
Blessed with martial talent,
he was wounded in battle at a young age.

09:10.925 --> 09:14.845
Every time someone asked, my mother
just gave that same phony introduction.

09:19.767 --> 09:22.687
And I did the same.

09:25.314 --> 09:26.691
I couldn’t contradict what we told Kengyo

09:26.774 --> 09:29.819
or disgrace my mother’s name now.

09:30.653 --> 09:34.115
So I hid my past and lived my days
as a Yamada disciple.

09:34.782 --> 09:36.742
I was ashamed of it.

09:37.535 --> 09:40.204
Your past doesn’t matter!

09:40.288 --> 09:42.957
That's not what's important, is it?
It's the present!

09:44.542 --> 09:46.294
That’s not what I meant.

09:46.377 --> 09:48.713
I warned you to behave
like a proper Yamada disciple.

09:48.796 --> 09:50.339
I am behaving!

09:50.423 --> 09:54.594
Don’t judge me by my upbringing.
See me for who I am, Senpai!

09:55.761 --> 09:58.097
It's Tenza and Shugen.
There they go again.

09:58.180 --> 09:59.849
Let them be. It's entertaining.

10:02.727 --> 10:04.103
Tenza laid himself bare,

10:04.186 --> 10:07.106
fearless and open. I envied him.

10:07.815 --> 10:10.276
He was accepted just as he was.

10:10.818 --> 10:12.653
I sensed potential in him.

10:15.072 --> 10:20.077
Man, Sensei, your swordsmanship
is seriously amazing!

10:20.161 --> 10:21.996
I admire you so much!

10:24.332 --> 10:25.499
No, that’s not right.

10:26.083 --> 10:28.127
You were the one I admired.

10:36.177 --> 10:39.055
I’ll kill you with my own hands!

10:39.138 --> 10:41.098
Even if it costs me my life!

10:51.359 --> 10:54.528
I can regenerate
while using the power of Kishikai.

10:54.612 --> 10:57.281
- You have no chance of win--
- Silence.

10:58.115 --> 11:01.702
That form, those flashy techniques,
they're all just cheap theatrics.

11:02.870 --> 11:04.413
You’re just focusing

11:04.497 --> 11:07.583
what little strength you have left
on appearances and showmanship.

11:07.667 --> 11:10.294
Soon your Tao will drop
to the level of a mere human.

11:11.003 --> 11:13.381
That poor performance won’t fool me.

11:14.382 --> 11:16.467
Neither side has the decisive edge
over the other.

11:17.343 --> 11:20.429
Which means from here on out,
it’s a quagmire.

11:20.513 --> 11:22.807
An ugly endurance match to the death.

11:23.766 --> 11:25.309
Are you ready?

11:29.146 --> 11:30.272
Sensei!

11:31.857 --> 11:32.983
Nurugai.

11:37.405 --> 11:39.240
Stay back.

11:39.323 --> 11:42.159
From here on, I’ll handle this alone.

11:43.786 --> 11:46.789
It’s too dangerous now.

11:49.917 --> 11:51.168
Damn it!

12:00.636 --> 12:03.848
Since I’m not his natural counter,
it’ll be a battle of attrition.

12:04.473 --> 12:08.561
So, it’s about how efficiently
I can make him burn Tao, huh?

12:09.311 --> 12:11.939
Instead of cutting him hundreds of times,

12:12.022 --> 12:14.191
wouldn’t it be easier to just
skewer him with your sword?

12:15.025 --> 12:15.943
True.

12:16.569 --> 12:18.571
Physically, that’s possible.

12:18.654 --> 12:22.700
The Tensen’s Tanden seems to be
like a seed inside the body.

12:23.409 --> 12:26.245
If we force them to regenerate
repeatedly and drain their Tao,

12:26.328 --> 12:27.705
impaling them would be efficient.

12:31.667 --> 12:33.586
Cut off their limbs.

12:34.753 --> 12:36.005
Or...

12:36.922 --> 12:40.342
extract the seed and skewer that alone.

12:41.177 --> 12:44.346
With our experience in Hiemontori,
it wouldn’t be difficult, would it?

12:45.556 --> 12:48.434
The question is whether we
can maintain the impalement.

12:48.517 --> 12:49.727
Oh, right.

12:49.810 --> 12:53.606
Just imagining it makes me sick.
I couldn’t do it.

13:04.074 --> 13:06.619
They regenerate. Vines extend.

13:06.702 --> 13:11.123
Sword gets pulled out. Even if you
pin them down, you’ll be obstructed.

13:12.166 --> 13:13.459
They'll penetrate you.

13:13.959 --> 13:15.211
Sensei!

13:19.882 --> 13:21.592
Weaker than I expected.

13:22.343 --> 13:24.261
Maybe because his Tao’s been drained.

13:25.346 --> 13:28.974
I told you, it would
come down to endurance.

13:29.058 --> 13:32.978
Will you run out of strength first,
or will I?

13:33.646 --> 13:35.397
This will settle it.

13:36.815 --> 13:39.985
If we both fall, I win!

13:53.624 --> 13:55.042
This level of pain...

13:55.834 --> 13:59.004
is nothing compared... to his final moments!

13:59.588 --> 14:01.507
Sensei, stop!

14:01.590 --> 14:03.384
If you go any further, you’ll die!

14:04.009 --> 14:04.885
Stay back!

14:06.720 --> 14:10.641
If this continues, I can take
the monster down with me!

14:10.724 --> 14:15.646
You must leave here now
and reunite with the others.

14:16.522 --> 14:19.233
I’ll stay behind.

14:21.193 --> 14:23.654
That’s not right.

14:24.613 --> 14:26.657
You’re smart, Sensei.

14:26.740 --> 14:29.159
You think things through.

14:29.243 --> 14:31.745
You’re someone who makes
the right decision, aren't you?

14:32.746 --> 14:34.623
This isn’t like you!

14:37.751 --> 14:38.669
When it happened...

14:40.462 --> 14:42.798
I instantly understood his scream.

14:44.633 --> 14:47.803
I grasped that he knew we couldn’t win
and wanted to avoid total annihilation.

14:48.637 --> 14:49.805
So I acted at once.

14:51.390 --> 14:54.059
It was the "right" decision.

14:55.769 --> 14:59.565
Why... did I choose what was right?

15:00.858 --> 15:03.319
Even if it was foolish,
I should have stayed with him.

15:05.863 --> 15:08.490
In his final moments,
how much regret did he feel?

15:08.574 --> 15:11.619
How much suffering
did he endure before he fell?

15:12.786 --> 15:14.788
I was the one who had to run.

15:15.539 --> 15:16.582
I can't forgive myself.

15:19.126 --> 15:21.253
Even when something
precious was to be lost,

15:22.171 --> 15:24.089
I chose what was right.

15:25.007 --> 15:26.216
I cannot forgive myself.

15:29.136 --> 15:30.804
These eyes cannot shed tears.

15:31.889 --> 15:32.848
Then...

15:33.515 --> 15:34.850
at the very least...

15:38.187 --> 15:39.438
Sensei!

15:40.814 --> 15:44.610
Leave this to me and hurry to the others!

15:45.277 --> 15:48.113
- No... But...
- Hurry!

15:48.948 --> 15:49.865
Hurry!

16:01.752 --> 16:05.005
Sensei, you’re just like I was back then.

16:06.215 --> 16:08.634
You lost someone you loved.

16:09.718 --> 16:11.428
You can’t forgive yourself.

16:17.685 --> 16:19.603
Unsure whether you should live or die,

16:20.479 --> 16:22.731
just like I was.

16:23.816 --> 16:26.485
I survived alone.

16:27.152 --> 16:29.238
Even though everyone died because of me.

16:35.077 --> 16:37.246
I don’t get it at all!

16:39.832 --> 16:42.501
So why do you have to die?!

16:46.338 --> 16:47.506
That’s right.

16:48.173 --> 16:50.342
If you don’t explain it right...

16:51.343 --> 16:52.845
If I can’t accept it...

16:54.221 --> 16:55.305
I...

16:56.473 --> 16:57.725
I...

17:07.860 --> 17:10.029
Te... Tenza...

17:10.654 --> 17:13.741
I... um... um...

17:15.159 --> 17:17.578
Sensei, I...

17:23.042 --> 17:26.128
Then there’s only one thing to do, right?

17:30.466 --> 17:31.633
Yeah!

17:43.854 --> 17:46.315
If you don’t explain it right,

17:46.398 --> 17:47.649
if I can’t accept it...

17:48.692 --> 17:50.277
I’m not going back!

17:54.073 --> 17:56.658
I can’t hear anything anymore.

17:57.910 --> 17:59.536
I don’t know how much time has passed

18:00.162 --> 18:02.122
or how much longer I can endure.

18:03.791 --> 18:06.752
All I can clearly feel is my life

18:07.377 --> 18:09.922
being slowly eaten away.

18:17.763 --> 18:20.265
Slowly. Which means

18:21.058 --> 18:23.685
the impalement worked.

18:25.312 --> 18:27.773
Tenza... Finally...

18:37.449 --> 18:38.575
Nuru...

18:54.508 --> 18:55.634
What are you doing?!

18:56.552 --> 18:58.637
I'm hugging you to restore your Tao!

19:00.055 --> 19:01.974
Now’s not the time for that!

19:04.184 --> 19:07.688
And besides! A girl shouldn’t
just embrace someone so casually!

19:07.771 --> 19:09.523
In more ways than one! Stop it!

19:10.649 --> 19:11.525
Huh?

19:12.317 --> 19:15.279
Now you’re starting to sound
like yourself again, Sensei.

19:17.406 --> 19:18.282
Look.

19:19.491 --> 19:23.078
He’s not dead,
but his regeneration’s slowed.

19:23.162 --> 19:25.789
At that rate, it’ll take him
a whole day to recover.

19:26.832 --> 19:29.042
All the more reason to finish him now.

19:29.126 --> 19:32.045
No. All the more reason to leave him be.

19:33.130 --> 19:36.049
If we get close again,
the vines will pierce us.

19:36.133 --> 19:38.552
Any more than this and you’ll die.

19:39.136 --> 19:41.805
Let’s go back to the others.

19:45.559 --> 19:47.686
I... can’t do that.

19:49.062 --> 19:52.232
If I don’t end him,
Tenza’s regrets won’t be put to rest.

19:53.609 --> 19:55.360
His suffering...

19:56.695 --> 19:57.821
That's not it.

19:59.448 --> 20:02.326
It’s not regret. It’s not suffering.

20:03.285 --> 20:04.286
It's not?

20:05.454 --> 20:08.332
When you were running
with me in your arms,

20:08.415 --> 20:09.583
I saw him.

20:10.417 --> 20:13.587
He was smiling.

20:14.421 --> 20:16.590
He was smiling as he watched us leave.

20:17.841 --> 20:21.220
You didn’t know that,
and you’ve been suffering all this time.

20:22.262 --> 20:24.765
It was because you
were carrying me. Sorry.

20:26.266 --> 20:27.601
It was a good smile.

20:28.769 --> 20:32.356
It was sad, but he looked so cool.

20:34.066 --> 20:35.442
So it wasn’t regret.

20:36.193 --> 20:37.861
That's not it, Sensei.

20:44.076 --> 20:48.413
We’ve only been talking about revenge.

20:48.497 --> 20:51.625
We haven’t really talked
about Tenza himself, have we?

20:52.918 --> 20:57.130
Tell me about him.
I want to know more about him.

20:58.423 --> 20:59.883
Let’s talk.

21:00.884 --> 21:03.428
After we get out of here alive.

21:26.243 --> 21:27.411
You’re right.

21:27.995 --> 21:31.915
Let’s end this. No more chasing after him.

21:34.418 --> 21:35.794
Let’s go to the others.

21:41.008 --> 21:42.968
Thank you, Nurugai.

21:44.094 --> 21:46.930
You gave me life.

21:55.188 --> 21:57.733
Maybe I’m the one
who should be calling you Sensei.

21:58.817 --> 22:00.193
I've opened my eyes now.

22:01.570 --> 22:02.779
You probably can’t hear me.

22:11.288 --> 22:13.707
Zhu Jin, they got you?

22:15.542 --> 22:17.711
NURUGAI, SHION

22:18.795 --> 22:19.880
Shion-dono.

22:24.509 --> 22:26.511
Will you reconsider?

22:27.220 --> 22:30.932
If this continues, we’ll only keep
losing the people precious to us.

22:31.558 --> 22:34.394
That would be far too tragic.

22:36.813 --> 22:37.814
Please...

22:47.574 --> 22:50.494
GABIMARU

24:21.918 --> 24:25.964
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman
